the Card Connect acquisition. A few follow-up items:

*

The QofE diligence period is complete and the findings were delivered last Friday (5/26). I have
provided a copy of the report to Geoff and Steve. Overall, favorable results with only a very modest
reduction to EBITDA. There has been no change in our favorable view of the acquisition.

*

RSM indicated the planned mid-July close date provided sufficient time to complete all
necessary controls and audit procedures. This assumes we get them all Card Connect financials and
supporting transaction documentation before month end.

*

RSM indicated that if the July date slips that all close period controls, standards, etc. will apply.

Attached are the July financials. The P&L variances is virtually all timing. Of particular note is the Amex
revenue was negatively impacted, as expected, by $632k because we processed fewer Amex transactions
due to higher volume of PIN debit. We had about $100k of non-recurring expenses in July, primarily
severance, retention, and other close related expenses. I expect our non-recurring will continue to increase
as we work towards full integration.
